schema.title: ErrorBody
schema.description: Detailed information about an error response.

errorCode.description: A code unique to this error.
errorCode.name: errorCode

status.description: The HTTP status code for this message (400, 401, 403, 404, 500, etc.)
status.name: status

correlationId.description: The correlation Id or context Id for this message. If left blank the Public API will look at the HTTP response header 'ININ-Correlation-Id' instead.
correlationId.name: correlationId

entityId.description: The ID of the entity this error refers to. Only used in BackendErrorBody instances within the errors array.
entityId.name: entityId

entityName.description: The name of the entity this error refers to. Only used in BackendErrorBody instances within the errors array.
entityName.name: entityName

userMessage.description: A customer friendly message. This should be a complete sentence, use proper grammar and only include information useful to a customer. This is not a dev message and should not include things like Org Id
userMessage.name: userMessage

userParamsMessage.description: This is the same as message except it uses template fields for variable replacement. For instance: 'User {username} was not found'
userParamsMessage.name: userParamsMessage

userParams.key.description: Used in conjunction with userParamsMessage. These are the template parameters. For instance: UserParam.key = 'username', UserParam.value = 'john.doe'
userParams.key.name: userParams.key

userParams.value.description: Used in conjunction with userParamsMessage. These are the template parameters. For instance: UserParam.key = 'username', UserParam.value = 'john.doe'
userParams.value.name: userParams.value

inputSchema.title: Flow input schema
inputSchema.description: Schema defining flow input parameters.  Property names map to flow scoped variables marked as a flow input.  If you do not supply a property value for an input variable, the variable value will be set to the initial value configured on it in the flow at flow startup.

outputSchema.title: Flow output schema
outputSchema.description: Schema defining flow output parameters.  Property names map to flow scoped variables marked as a flow output.
